request.description:
Get the security question for an account to begin the password reset process. The URL format is /user/forgot?email={email}, where {email} is the email address of the account that needs its password reset.

No JWT authentication is required.

Get the security question for an account to begin the password reset process. The URL format is /user/forgot?email={email}, where {email} is the email address of the account that needs its password reset.

No JWT authentication is required.

If successful, a JWT token will be returned. This token is ONLY an access token to reset the password of the user id encoded in the token and will not work on any other endpoints. 

IMPORTANT NOTE: This token expiry's 5 minutes after it is issued. If it expires, you must restart the password reset process.

Provide a new password for the user in the body.

The JWT token returned from the security question answer endpoint is required here.

Create a new workspace. The user that creates the workspace automatically becomes the admin of the workspace

You will need to include the user's JWT token in the "Authorization" header.

Get the list of workspaces that the user belongs to

You will need to include the user's JWT token in the "Authorization" header.

Create a new display. Provide the name of the display and the workspace ID that the display should be added to. Only users who have access to a workspace can add displays to it

You will need to include the user's JWT token in the "Authorization" header.

Get a list of all displays that belong to a workspace. The URL format is /displays/{workspaceId}. Only users who have access to a workspace can view its displays.

You will need to include the user's JWT token in the "Authorization" header.

Login with a username and password.

JWT token will be returned to access other endpoints that require authentication

Get information about a user.

You will need to include the user's JWT token in the "Authorization" header.

The JWT access token is set to expire ever 30 minutes. Use this endpoint to get a new token (aka, another 30 minutes of access). You must call this endpoint before the current token expires, otherwise you will have log in again.

You will need to include the user's JWT token in the "Authorization" header.
